{
  "design_notes": "The chart is designed as a comfortable StepMania Medium (level 5-6 equivalent) that tightly mirrors the track's energetic peaks and valleys. The intro sets a sparse, steady rhythm before dropping into S1 where eighth-note streams and accent jumps emphasize the key downbeats. S2 builds tension with a moderate quarter-note walk with light crossovers. S3 and S4 act as the main drop sequence, boosting jump density and utilizing long-hold freezes that allow the player's other foot to step along with the vocal syncopations. After S5's breathing room, S6 and S7 replicate the heavy beat-driven intensity of the drops. S8 tapers off with a sparse, rhythmically accurate outro that prevents any long dead pauses, ensuring players stay engaged right up to the final beat.",
